Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and brown, cloudy urine, suggesting possible renal dysfunction (likely glomerular) and impaired tubular reabsorption. Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, making diabetes less likely. Mildly low erythrocyte count may indicate early anemia. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible acute or chronic kidney disease and underlying causes. No evidence of infection or hematuria.
